  File: about.hbs
  Description: Template for displaying the "About Us" information section.
  Author: Daniel Gorelkin
  Version: 1.2
  Created: 2025-08-22
  Updated: 2025-11-10
  Template Credits: freewebsitetemplates.com

  Purpose:
    - Part of the Travlr CMS project
    - Responsible for rendering the About Us content dynamically
    - Displays company information, crew details, amenities,
      community introduction, and template details

  Expected Input Structure:
    about_us: {
      content: {
        paragraph_1: String,
        paragraph_2: String
      },
      crews: String,
      amenities: String,
      community: String,
      details: String
    }
===================================================================== -->

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

  <!-- Shared HEAD partial containing metadata, styles, and scripts.
  Loaded using handlebars from the head.hbs partial file. -->
  {{> head }}

  <body>
    <div id="background">

      <div id="page">

        <!-- Header partial (logo, navigation, login option).
        Loaded via header.hbs and shared across all pages. -->
        {{> header }}

        <!-- Main content block for About Us section.
        Uses the "about_us" object passed from the about.js controller. -->
        <div id="contents">
          <div class="box">
            <div>
              <div class="body">

                <!-- Page Title -->
                <h1>About Me - Daniel Gorelkin</h1>

                <!-- Subheading and dynamic introductory content -->
                <h3>ePortfolio Setup</h3>
                <p>{{{ about_us.content.paragraph_1 }}}</p>
                <p>{{{ about_us.content.paragraph_2 }}}</p>

                <hr>

                <!-- Crew and Amenities information block -->
                <div class="ads">
                  <h3>Category One: Software Engineering and Design</h3>
                  <p>
                    The artifact enhanced under this category is the Travlr mid-course milestone project from the CS-465 Full Stack Development class.
                    The redesigned version adopts a mobile-first approach to ensure full compatibility across mobile and desktop devices.

                    Enhancements include:
                    <br><br>
                    • User account creation<br>
                    • Two-step authentication (2SV)<br>
                    • User login system<br>
                    • Cart functionality for booking and order management<br>
                    • UI redesign for improved professionalism and usability<br>
                    • Migration from a local database to MongoDB Atlas<br>
                    • Testing and deployment in a production environment<br><br>

                    <strong>Skills Demonstrated:</strong><br>
                    Updating software architecture, implementing authentication, cloud database migration, and applying modern secure design practices.<br><br>

                    <strong>Aligned Course Outcomes:</strong><br>
                    Outcome 2 – Apply innovative tools and techniques to deliver value and meet industry goals.<br>
                    Outcome 5 – Develop a security mindset to identify vulnerabilities and protect user data.
                  </p>

                  <h3>Category Two: Algorithms and Data Structures</h3>
                  <p>
                    The second enhancement extends the Travlr project by adding algorithmic intelligence to improve performance and search efficiency.

                    Enhancement steps include:
                    <br><br>
                    • Implementing server-side indexing and optimized MongoDB queries for faster results<br>
                    • Developing multi-criteria filtering algorithms (destination, price, rating, etc.)<br>
                    • Improving responsiveness and overall UX through algorithmic optimization<br><br>

                    <strong>Skills Demonstrated:</strong><br>
                    Implementing optimized search and filtering algorithms, applying algorithmic principles, and communicating technical results effectively.<br><br>

                    <strong>Aligned Course Outcomes:</strong><br>
                    Outcome 3 – Design and evaluate computing solutions using algorithmic principles.<br>
                    Outcome 4 – Use innovative tools and techniques to deliver professional, industry-level functionality.
                  </p>

                  <h3>Category Three: Databases</h3>
                  <p>
                    This enhancement focuses on migrating the Travlr data layer to a scalable cloud environment using MongoDB Atlas.

                    Enhancement steps include:
                    <br><br>
                    • Creating and configuring a secure MongoDB Atlas cluster with role-based access control<br>
                    • Migrating all data from the local database to the cloud<br>
                    • Developing a secure RESTful API for front-end connectivity<br>
                    • Enabling collaborative workflows for admins and analysts using tools such as Power BI or Tableau<br><br>

                    <strong>Skills Demonstrated:</strong><br>
                    Designing and deploying modern databases, managing scalability trade-offs, and enabling secure collaboration.<br><br>

                    <strong>Aligned Course Outcomes:</strong><br>
                    Outcome 1 – Build collaborative environments for diverse audiences to support decision-making.<br>
                    Outcome 4 – Use innovative computing tools to create value and achieve industry goals.
                  </p>
                </div>

                <!-- Community message -->
                <h2>Be Part of Our Community</h2>
                <p>
                  Join a growing network of learners, developers, and professionals committed to building modern, secure, and scalable applications.
                  The Travlr enhancement demonstrates how thoughtful design and technology can create meaningful, real-world value.
                </p>

                <!-- Template details -->
                <h2>Community Details</h2>
                <p>
                  This project showcases full-stack development, database engineering, user-centric design principles, and secure software practices.
                  It reflects a commitment to continuous improvement, collaborative development, and industry-aligned innovation.
                </p>

                <br>
                <h2><strong>ePortfolio Overall Skill Set</strong></h2>
                <h3>This ePortfolio demonstrates my ability to design, develop, and enhance full-stack web applications with strong emphasis on:</h3>
                <p>
                  • High-quality user experience and responsive interfaces<br>
                  • Secure data management and cloud-based integration<br>
                  • Algorithmic problem-solving and efficient data handling<br>
                  • It highlights how I apply computer science principles and techniques to solve real-world problems and deliver professional, standards-compliant solutions.<br>
                </p>

                <h4>Code Review Focus</h4>
                <p>
                  • Applying algorithmic principles to improve performance<br>
                  • Writing secure, maintainable, and scalable code<br>
                  • Following best practices and modern development standards<br>
                </p>

                <h4>Narratives Focus</h4>
                <p>
                  • Communicating technical details to diverse audiences<br>
                  • Explaining design trade-offs and rationale<br>
                  • Connecting development choices to professional outcomes<br>
                </p>

                <h4>Professional Self-Assessment Focus</h4>
                <p>
                  • Reflecting on growth in technical and professional skills<br>
                  • Integrating academic learning into real-world practice<br>
                  • Demonstrating readiness for professional roles and employment readability<br>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- Footer partial (links, navigation, admin login).
      Loaded via footer.hbs and shared across all pages. -->
      {{> footer }}

    </div>

    <script src="/javascripts/registerAndLogin.js"></script>

  </body>
</html>
